  "text": "Found all five Kafka consumer group partition assignment strategy implementations in the apache/kafka repository. These are located in the clients module:\n\n1. **RangeAssignor** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/RangeAssignor.java): Implements range-based partition assignment on a per-topic basis, laying out partitions in numeric order and consumers in lexicographic order, then dividing partitions evenly.\n\n2. **RoundRobinAssignor** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/RoundRobinAssignor.java): Implements round-robin partition assignment across all available partitions and consumers, providing uniform distribution when all consumer subscriptions are identical.\n\n3. **StickyAssignor** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/StickyAssignor.java): Extends AbstractStickyAssignor and implements sticky assignment that balances partitions while preserving as many existing assignments as possible during rebalancing. Uses eager rebalancing protocol.\n\n4. **CooperativeStickyAssignor** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/CooperativeStickyAssignor.java): A cooperative version of StickyAssignor that follows the same sticky assignment logic but supports cooperative rebalancing protocol instead of eager rebalancing.\n\n5. **AbstractPartitionAssignor** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractPartitionAssignor.java): The abstract base class implementing ConsumerPartitionAssignor, providing common functionality for partition assignment including partition count collection, rack-aware assignment support, and the MemberInfo nested class for member metadata."
}

